headlines.description: — Miles Bridges scored 31 points, Gordon Hayward added 24 and the Charlotte Hornets beat the Orlando Magic 120-111 on Wednesday night for their fourth win in five games.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bridges, Hayward lead Hornets past Magic 120-111

headlines.description: — Montrezl Harrell scored 25 points on 10-of-13 shooting and had 11 rebounds in the Washington Wizards' 116-107 victory over the Boston Celtics on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Montrezl Harrell helps Wizards beat Celtics, 116-107

headlines.description: — Bam Adebayo had 24 points and nine rebounds to lead the Miami Heat to a 106-93 victory over the Brooklyn Nets on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Adebayo has 24, Heat pull away to beat Nets 106-93

headlines.description: — Fred VanVleet and the Raptors pushed around the Indiana Pacers to pick up a long-awaited home win.
headlines.shortLinkText: VanVleet scores 26, Raptors beat Pacers for 1st home win

events.name: Atlanta Hawks at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Trae Young and the Atlanta Hawks are grinding out victories early this season without the offensive rhythm they are confident is still to come.
headlines.shortLinkText: Young's 31 points lift Hawks past Pelicans, 102-99

headlines.description: — D’Angelo Russell scored 29 points, Karl-Anthony Towns and Anthony Edwards each added 25, and the Minnesota Timberwolves held off the short-handed Milwaukee Bucks 113-108 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Russell, Towns lead T'Wolves to rare win at Milwaukee

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander scored 27 points, and the Oklahoma City Thunder rallied from 26 points down to beat the Los Angeles Lakers 123-115 on Wednesday night for their first win of the season.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gilgeous-Alexander, Thunder rally from 26 down to top Lakers

headlines.description: — Their 10-point lead had evaporated in less than three minutes and it looked like the same ol' dreadful Sacramento Kings were about to blow another winnable game.
headlines.shortLinkText: Barnes hits 3 at buzzer, Kings sink Suns 110-107

events.name: Memphis Grizzlies at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — With a productive third quarter, Damian Lillard began to find a groove again.
headlines.shortLinkText: McCollum has 25 points, Blazers beat Grizzlies 116-96

headlines.description: — Collin Sexton scored 26 points, Darius Garland added 16 and the Cleveland Cavaliers led all the way in beating the Los Angeles Clippers 92-79 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cavs win 92-79, 1st road victory over Clippers since 2016
